                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17456</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-13T10:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1916, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>During conference with Secretary Foreign Relations this morning he stated to me:
                    “Should war result over the Columbus affair the position of the United States
                    would be that of assisting the reactionaries as against the Constitutionalist
                    Government.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Belt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
